article.headline: Wagner 72, Loyola Marymount 51
article.story: NEW YORK -- Joey Mundweiler scored 16 points to help Wagner extend Loyola Marymount's winless streak to five games with a 72-51 win Monday night. Jamal Smith and Llew Radford each had 12 points for the Seahawks (3-1), who led almost from the start and were up 36-28 at halftime. LaRon Armstead led the Lions (0-5) with 11 points, and Ashley Hamilton scored 10.
